  "id": "019d442a-0a15-7ca3-b9db-5261630eafd8",
  "content": "<span style=\"color: var(--accent-amber); font-weight: 700;\">Hours of wasted work avoided.</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">08 / 09</div>\n</div>\n<!-- SLIDE 9: TAKEAWAYS -->\n<div class=\"slide\" style=\"background: linear-gradient(160deg, #0f172a 0%, #1a2332 50%, #0f172a 100%);\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">Key Takeaways</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 36px;\">\n    What I Learned\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 28px; margin-bottom: 40px;\">\n    <div style=\"display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 32px; flex-shrink: 0;\">&#127919;</div>\n      <div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700;\">Roles change everything</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 22px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;\">\n          A generic \"review this\" catches surface issues. A PM persona catches incomplete work. A Security persona catches leaked secrets. The role defines what gets found.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 32px; flex-shrink: 0;\">&#128200;</div>\n      <div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700;\">Independent context windows matter</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 22px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;\">\n          One reviewer with five roles collapses to one perspective. Five separate subagents find different things because they think independently.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 32px; flex-shrink: 0;\">&#128196;</div>\n      <div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700;\">Review designs, not just code</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size: 22px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;\">\n          The highest-leverage reviews happen before implementation. A flaw caught in a spec costs minutes. In code, it costs hours.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>",
